      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Resistance opposes the flow of current in a way that dissipates energy as heat, similar to a regular resistor. Reactance, on the other hand, is the opposition to current flow caused by energy storage elements like inductors and capacitors. You need both to calculate impedance because impedance is the total opposition to AC current, combining the energy-dissipating effect of resistance with the energy-storing effect of reactance. Think of impedance as the full picture of how a circuit resists the flow of alternating current.",
